xe xf pd yk yl bg" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">Avoid using CSS classes u=
nless they are specifically meant for testing (framework-generated class na=
mes often change).</li><li id=3D"5ba1" class=3D"wi wj st wk b wl ym wn wo w=
p yn wr ws wt yo wv ww wx yp wz xa xb yq xd xe xf pd yk yl bg" data-selecta=
ble-paragraph=3D"">Prefer unique IDs for elements whenever possible.</li><l=
i id=3D"4641" class=3D"wi wj st wk b wl ym wn wo wp yn wr ws wt yo wv ww wx=
 yp wz xa xb yq xd xe xf pd yk yl bg" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">Use ac=
cessibility-driven selectors (aria-labels, role attributes, etc.).</li><li =
id=3D"a546" class=3D"wi wj st wk b wl ym wn wo wp yn wr ws wt yo wv ww wx y=
p wz xa xb yq xd xe xf pd yk yl bg" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">In moder=
n front-end apps (React, Angular, Vue), talk to your dev team about adding =
<code class=3D"dw yr ys yt yu b">data-test</code> attributes for reliable s=
electors.</li></ul><p id=3D"4d66" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph wi wj st =
wk b wl wm wn wo wp wq wr ws wt wu wv ww wx wy wz xa xb xc xd xe xf fi bg" =
data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">Good selectors =3D stable tests. Stable test=
